<h1 style="text-align: center; font-size: 16pt;">ATTORNEY REVIEW AND COORDINATION CONSENT</h1>
<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 10pt; color: #555;">
For Surplus Recovery Service Agreement No: {{caseNumber}}<br>
Effective Date: {{formatDate effectiveDate}}
</p>

<hr style="margin: 20px 0;">

<div style="background: #d4edda; border: 1px solid #28a745; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
<p style="margin: 0;"><strong>ATTORNEY REVIEW NEEDED:</strong> Your claim in {{jurisdictionState}}{{#if jurisdictionCounty}}, {{jurisdictionCounty}} County{{/if}} requires involvement of a licensed attorney. This may be due to a requirement for court filing, contested ownership, lien resolution, or other legal proceedings.</p>
</div>

<h2>1. PURPOSE</h2>

<p>1.1. {{companyName}} ("Company") has determined that the recovery claim associated with Agreement No. {{caseNumber}} requires the involvement of a licensed attorney for one or more of the following reasons:</p>

<p style="padding-left: 20px;">
&#9744; Judicial motion or court filing is required by the jurisdiction<br>
&#9744; Contested heirs or ownership dispute<br>
&#9744; Lien, judgment, or encumbrance on the surplus funds<br>
&#9744; Complex title or chain-of-ownership issues<br>
&#9744; Other: _______________________________________________
</p>

<p>1.2. <strong>The Company is NOT a law firm and does NOT provide legal advice.</strong> The attorney involved in your case is an independent licensed professional and is not an employee of the Company.</p>

<h2>2. ATTORNEY COORDINATION</h2>

<p>2.1. The Company will coordinate with a licensed attorney in the applicable jurisdiction to handle the legal aspects of your claim. The attorney will act as your legal representative for the limited purpose of the claim proceedings.</p>

<p>2.2. <strong>You are free to choose your own attorney.</strong> If you have your own attorney or wish to retain a different attorney, please notify the Company in writing and the Company will work with your chosen attorney instead.</p>

<p>2.3. The Company will share relevant case information and documentation with the attorney for the sole purpose of processing your claim. This includes your personal information, claim details, and supporting documents.</p>

<h2>3. FEES AND COSTS</h2>

<p>3.1. The attorney's fees for handling the legal aspects of your claim are included in the Success Fee described in the Agreement. You will not be charged additional attorney fees by the Company.</p>

<p>3.2. However, certain court filing fees, service fees, or other costs required by the court may apply. If such costs arise, the Company will notify you in advance and seek your approval before incurring them.</p>

<p>3.3. If you choose to retain your own attorney, you are responsible for any fees charged by your chosen attorney separately from the Success Fee owed to the Company.</p>

<h2>4. WHAT THIS MEANS FOR YOU</h2>

<p style="padding-left: 20px;">
• Your claim requires legal proceedings — this is common for certain types of surplus recovery<br>
• A licensed attorney will handle the legal filings on your behalf<br>
• You will not pay additional attorney fees through the Company<br>
• You have the right to choose your own attorney at any time<br>
• The Company will keep you informed about all legal proceedings<br>
• The "no legal advice" clause in the Agreement applies to the Company, not to the attorney
</p>

<h2>5. CONSENT</h2>

<p>By signing below, you consent to the following:</p>

<p style="padding-left: 20px;">
(a) You understand that your claim requires attorney involvement.<br>
(b) You consent to the Company sharing your case information with a licensed attorney.<br>
(c) You understand that you may choose your own attorney at any time.<br>
(d) You understand that the attorney is independent from the Company.<br>
(e) You understand that court costs (if any) may apply and will be communicated to you in advance.
</p>

